&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/889&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/889&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2321&quot; title=&quot;The seed for the SVM classifier is currently static&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-2321&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-2321&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ml&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;  The seed for the SVM classifier is currently static&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    The seed for the SVM algorithm in FlinkML has a default value of 0, meaning that if it&apos;s not set, we always have the same seed when running the algorithm.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    What should happen instead is that if the seed is not set, it should be a random number.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This PR introduces a random seed instead.&lt;/p&gt;

